  "text": "where δ(·) is the Dirac delta function and u(·) is the unit step function. Note that due to the Dirac delta function system NSNR is equal to zero with probability [1 − P NSNR (β NSNR )]. As seen from (2) and (3), the system SNR γ NSNR is calculated by multiplying the system NSNR η NSNR with the γ k = h H k h k . In order to derive the system SNR for the NSNR scheme, we need to use the Chi-square PDF of the γ k given as follows [CITATION_1] : The product γ NSNR = η NSNR γ is a continuous random variable whose PDF can be found using Finally, the PDF of system SNR for the proposed NSNR scheme can be obtained as follows:",
